<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
Berlese created the genus in 1913; he published no diagnosis, but mentioned &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palliatus">Nothrus palliatus</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bistriatus">N. bistriatus K.</taxonomicName>
)&quot; as type of the genus, and added 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatus">Nothrus punctatus L. Koch</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peltifer">N. peltifer C. L. Koch</taxonomicName>
. As Sellnick &amp; Forsslund (1955) already mentioned, 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" genus.completionEvidence="missing, matching species" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palliatus">palliatus</taxonomicName>
is the nymph of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peltifer">peltifer</taxonomicName>
(syn. 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Hermanniidae" genus="Hermannia" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bistriata">bistriata</taxonomicName>
sensu Nicolet) so that the correct name of the type-species is now 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Platynothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peltifer">Platynothrus peltifer</taxonomicName>
. I have added one species (
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Platynothrus" genus.completionEvidence="missing" genus.completionRound="1" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustior">robustior</taxonomicName>
), which Berlese described as a 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Heminothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heminothrus</taxonomicName>
. As mentioned above I restricted 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Platynothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Platynothrus</taxonomicName>
to species of which the notogaster shows distinct dorsal ridges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
